The paper deals with scene parsing, which is a computer vision task, and proposes a new network architecture to improve performance. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of context in the network, which is a common topic in machine learning and deep learning research, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves natural language processing techniques, such as measuring similarity between features, which could place it in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses multiple modules to build a network, which could place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
